<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/628> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #628" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Prosecuted L. Manlius Imperiosus, Dict. 363, on charges variously reported in our sources: 1. remaining Dictator when his religius duty was done; 2. remaining in office beyond his legal term; 3. raising a levy with too great severity; 4. mistreatment of his son, the future T. Manlius Torquatus, who forced the Tribune to give up the prosecution (Cic. Off. 3.112; Liv. 7.3.4-5; Val. Max. 5.4.3; 6.9.1; Sen. Ben. 3.37.4; App. Samn. 2; Auct. Vir. Ill. 28; Zon. 7.24; see RE s. v. \"Manlius,\" no. 54). See Lübker, no. 1." .
